# Task Workflow

Every task — feature, fix, refactor — follows this workflow. No exceptions.

## Before Starting
1. Create a branch from `main`: `git checkout -b <type>/<short-name>`
   - `feat/` — new feature
   - `fix/` — bug fix
   - `refactor/` — structural change, no new behavior
   - `chore/` — config, deps, tooling
2. State the goal in one sentence
3. List the files/layers that will be affected
4. Get user confirmation before writing code

## While Working
- One logical change per commit — don't bundle unrelated work
- If touching multiple layers (schema → service → component → API), commit after completing each layer
- Never modify files outside the agreed scope without asking
- Run the dev server and check for errors after significant changes

## After Completing
1. Verify the app runs without errors
2. Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` if any files, folders, or patterns changed
3. Update `ROADMAP.md` — move the task from "In Progress" to **"Review"** (never straight to Done)
4. Update or create the feature card in `docs/features/` if a feature was added or changed
5. Summarize: what changed, which files, and any follow-up needed
6. Do NOT merge to `main` without explicit user permission
7. Only move to "Done" after the user approves and says to merge

## Branch Naming Examples
- `feat/script-parser` — adding the script parsing feature
- `fix/character-sync` — fixing a bug in character data sync
- `refactor/timeline-store` — restructuring timeline state management
- `chore/update-prisma` — updating a dependency
